# Database Architecture

## Overview
Database is **optional** — the server boots and runs without any `DATABASE_URL` configured. When a URL is provided, Prisma connects automatically.

## Default: SQLite
- Zero-config, file-based
- Set `DATABASE_URL="file:./data/app.db"` (or the HA path `/data/app.db`)
- Schema uses `provider = "sqlite"` by default

## Optional: PostgreSQL
- Change `provider` in `server/prisma/schema.prisma` to `"postgresql"`
- Set `DATABASE_URL` to a PostgreSQL connection string
- Some column types differ (e.g., `@db.Uuid`, `@db.Timestamptz` are PG-only)
- Use `docker compose up -d` for a local PG instance

## Connection
- `server/database/core/connection.ts` — dynamic import of PrismaClient, graceful fallback if DB is unavailable
- `getPrismaClient()` returns `null` when DB is disabled
- `getConnectionStatus()` includes a `disabled` flag

## Commands
- `pnpm --filter @ha-addon/server db:migrate` — Create migration
- `pnpm --filter @ha-addon/server db:migrate:deploy` — Apply migrations (**use in production**: Home Assistant `run.sh`, standalone `run-standalone.sh`, releases)
- `pnpm --filter @ha-addon/server db:generate` — Generate Prisma client
- `pnpm --filter @ha-addon/server db:push` — Push schema to DB (**local dev only**; do not use for add-on/standalone—can drop columns without running backfill SQL and fails on data-loss prompts)
- `pnpm --filter @ha-addon/server db:studio` — Visual DB browser
